sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Usage Of Web Request Commands And Cmdlets - ScriptBlock
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the use of various web request commands with commandline tools and Windows PowerShell cmdlets (including aliases) via PowerShell scriptblock logs

match_context.values:
@{ScriptBlockText=function Install-GnuPg {
	
	<#
	.SYNOPSIS
		This function installed the GnuPg for Windows application.  It the installer file is not in
		the DownloadFolderPath, the function will download the file from the Internet and then execute a silent installation.
	.PARAMETER  DownloadFolderPath
		The folder path where you'd like to download the GnuPg for Windows installer into.

	.PARAMETER  DownloadUrl
		The URL that will be used to download the EXE setup installer.

	.EXAMPLE
		PS> Instal [TRUNCATED]; MessageTotal=1; ScriptBlockId=fa0dbbf2-613f-4298-ab12-5075b50af5ad; Path=C:\Users\gZrapWtUFpeE\AppData\Local\Temp\adcb78b386aa780a9668219a199bbb8b.ps1; MessageNumber=1; EventID=4104}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Potential Binary Or Script Dropper Via PowerShell
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects PowerShell creating a binary executable or a script file.
Detects execution of wmic utility with the "computersystem" flag in order to obtain information about the machine such as the domain, username, model, etc.

match_context.values: @{Product=Microsoft\xae Windows\xae Operating System; CurrentDirectory=C:\Users\george\Desktop\; OriginalFileName=wmic.exe; Hashes=MD5=EC80E603E0090B3AC3C1234C2BA43A0F,SHA256=D368BCB7934DB0C53D1E7277DCB47AF2B709253CBF0EEE9869EE7E17ED226EA3,IMPHASH=59A9108CA1CECC9147C5FBAB104EBF33; Description=WMI Commandline Utility; FileVersion=10.0.17134.1 (WinBuild.160101.0800); ParentCommandLine="C:\Windows\System32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0\powershell.exe" -noLogo -ExecutionPolicy unrestricted -file "C:\Users\george\Desktop\scripttodo.ps1"; CommandLine="C:\Windows\System32\Wbem\WMIC.exe" computersystem get domain; EventID=1; ParentImage=C:\Windows\System32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0\powershell.exe; IntegrityLevel=High; Image=C:\Windows\System32\wbem\WMIC.exe; Company=Microsoft Corporation}
